🖥️ Server kya hota hai?
Server ek power ful computer ya system hota hai jo dusre computers (clients) ko service deta hai.
📱 Real-life example:
Tum browser me YouTube open karte ho
Tumhara laptop/mobile = Client
YouTube ka system = Server
👉 Tum request bhejte ho → Server response deta hai (video, data, etc.)


🧩 IT me Server ke Types

1. 🌐 Web Server
Website serve karta hai
Example: HTML pages bhejna
Ex: Apache, Nginx

2. 📦 Application Server
Business logic handle karta hai
Backend code run karta hai (Java Spring Boot etc.)
👉 Tum jo Java backend bana rahe ho → wo application server pe run hota hai


3. 🗄️ Database Server
Data store karta hai
Example: MySQL, PostgreSQL

4. 📁 File Server
Files store aur share karta hai

5. 📧 Mail Server
Emails handle karta hai



⚙️ Serverful vs Serverless (IMPORTANT 🔥)

🏗️ 1. Serverful kya hota hai?
👉 Isme tumhe server manage karna padta hai
✔ Tum kya handle karte ho:
Server setup
CPU, RAM manage
Scaling
Deployment
Maintenance.
📌 Example:
Tum AWS EC2 pe server lete ho
Usme Java app deploy karte ho
✅ Advantages (Serverful)
Full control (OS, memory, config)
Customization possible
Long-running apps ke liye best.
❌ Disadvantages (Serverful)
Maintenance ka tension 😓
Scaling manually karna padta hai
Cost waste ho sakta hai (idle server bhi charge hota hai).

⚡ 2. Serverless kya hota hai?
👉 Serverless me bhi server hota hai, but tumhe manage nahi karna padta
👉 Cloud provider sab handle karta hai
✔ Tum kya karte ho:
Sirf code likhte ho
Baaki sab automatic (scaling, deployment, infra)
📌 Example:
AWS Lambda
Firebase Functions.
✅ Advantages (Serverless)
No server management 🚀
Auto scaling (traffic aaye ya na aaye)
Pay only when used 💰
Fast development
❌ Disadvantages (Serverless)
Limited control
Cold start issue (first request slow)
Long-running tasks ke liye ideal nahi
Vendor lock-in (AWS pe dependent ho jaoge).


⚙️ Scaling kya hota hai?
👉 Jab users ya traffic badhta hai, to system ko strong banana padta hai Is process ko Scaling bolte hain.


🧱 1. Vertical Scaling (Scale UP) kya hota hai?
👉 Ek hi machine ko powerful banana
📌 Example:
RAM increase (8GB → 32GB)
CPU upgrade
Storage badhana.
🧠 Real-life example:
Socho:
Tum ek dukaan chala rahe ho
Customers badh gaye
👉 Tum ek hi dukaan ko bada kar dete ho (AC, zyada staff, bada space)
✅ Advantages
Simple implementation 👍
Code change ki zarurat nahi
Easy to manage
❌ Disadvantages
Limit hoti hai (kitna upgrade karoge?)
Expensive 💰
Single point of failure ⚠️ (server down = sab down)

🌐 2. Horizontal Scaling (Scale OUT) kya hota hai?
👉 Multiple servers add karna
📌 Example:
1 server → 5 servers
Load balancer use karke traffic distribute
🧠 Real-life example:
Ek dukaan ki jagah 5 dukaan khol li
👉 Customers alag-alag jagah serve ho rahe hain
✅ Advantages
Highly scalable 🚀
Fault tolerant (1 server down → baaki chalte rahenge)
High traffic ke liye best (like Flipkart, Amazon)
❌ Disadvantages
Complex setup 😓
Load balancing required
Distributed system handle karna padta hai


------------------------------------THREAD-----------------
🧠 Task kya hota hai (Computer me)?
👉 Task = koi bhi kaam jo computer perform karta hai
🍽️ Real-life example
Socho tum:
YouTube dekh rahe ho 🎥
Background me file download ho rahi hai 📥
Music bhi chal raha hai 🎵
👉 Ye teeno alag-alag tasks hain.
Computer me task ka matlab ho sakta hai:
Ek program run hona
Ek process
Ek thread ka kaam


















🔷 Common System Design Patterns (Industry Use) ?
1️⃣ Layered Architecture Pattern (Basic) : Application ko layers me divide karna. Architecture:

Controller Layer
   |
Service Layer
   |
Repository / DAO Layer
   |
Database

2️⃣ Microservices Architecture Pattern ⭐ (Most Important) :
Application ko small independent services me tod dena.Full Architecture:

Client
  |
  v
Load Balancer
  |
  v
API Gateway
  |
  +-------------------+
  |                   |
User Service     Order Service     Payment Service
  |                   |                   |
 User DB           Order DB           Payment DB





